   Janino by janino-compiler .syntaxHighlighter.xml { padding: 6px 12px 6px 12px; line-height: 1em; } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .plain { color: #b9bdb6; } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .spaces { } .syntaxHighlighter.xml .keyword { color: #5ba1cf; } Janino A super-small, super-fast Java compiler View the Project on GitHub janino-compiler/janino Download ZIP File Browse JAVADOC View On GitHub Breaking news! Janino is now "Tee-ware", which means that the applicable license is still BSD, but you are free to buy a fan t-shirt on Teespring (one per CPU, or as many as you want ðŸ˜‰). Support the software development and show your appreciation by purchasing Janino merch! Janino is a super-small, super-fast Java compiler. Janino can not only compile a set of source files to a set of class files like JAVAC, but also compile a Java expression , a block , a class body , one .java file or a set of .java files in memory, load the bytecode and execute it directly in the running JVM. JANINO is integrated with Apache Commons JCI ("Java Compiler Interface") and JBoss Rules / Drools. JANINO can also be used for static code analysis or code manipulation . Table of Contents Getting Started Properties Requirements Limitations License Download Packages Security / integrity Installation Examples Documentation Change Log JAVADOC Books Links Basic Examples Janino as an Expression Evaluator Janino as a Script Evaluator Janino as a Class Body Evaluator Janino as a Simple Compiler Janino as a Compiler Advanced Examples Janino as a Source Code Class Loader jsh - the Java shell Janino as a Command-Line Java Compiler Janino as an ANT Compiler Janino as a TOMCAT Compiler Janino as a Code Analyser Janino as a Code Manipulator Alternative Compiler Implementations Security Debugging Contact Reporting bugs Requesting support Requesting new features Feedback Developers Source Code Repository Contributing Getting Started What's this all about? Check out this PDF presentation for a quick start. (Notice that some of